The paper focuses on analyzing the behavior of urban migrants in their initial period in a city and predicting their likelihood of leaving. This involves the use of telecommunication logs and housing price data, which are relevant to the sub-categories of social and information sciences (cs.SI), computational social science (cs.CY), statistical learning (cs.SD), social and economic networks (cs.SOC), and human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
